id: pm-qo36
title: "Extension API missing self-identity accessor: extensions cannot read their own name, layer, or version at activation"
description: "The ExtensionApi interface (extension-types.ts line 754) exposes only register* methods and hooks.*. An extension's activate(api) function has no way to read its own manifest metadata (name, version, layer) from the api object. Authors must either embed it redundantly in-module or access the file-system manifest. A read-only `api.manifest` or `api.extension` property (name, version, layer, capabilities, pm_min_version) would allow extensions to emit self-identifying logs, gate on their own version, and produce better error messages without duplicating manifest data."
type: Feature
status: closed
priority: 3
tags[4]: "area:extensions","area:sdk",dx,extensibility
created_at: "2026-06-07T10:05:01.492Z"
updated_at: "2026-06-08T13:51:50.961Z"
author: audit-platform-agent
acceptance_criteria: "- Extension `activate(api)` exposes the extension's own name, layer, and version (e.g. api.extension)\n- Available at activation without re-reading the manifest\n- SDK types + docs updated; covered by a test"
parent: pm-ugqx
risk: low
confidence: high
close_reason: ExtensionApi now exposes read-only frozen api.extension self-identity (name/layer/version/capabilities/pm_min_version/pm_max_version/source_package) built in createExtensionApi. Documented + tested.
body: ""
